    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-10-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-10-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1331"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1331">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 701.6311/173</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The</hi>
                    <gloss type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Department of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                    <gloss type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Austro-Hungarian Embassy</hi>
                    </gloss>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 1, 1915</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department of State presents its compliments to the Imperial and Royal
                    Austro-Hungarian Embassy and has the honor to enclose herewith copies of two
                        notes<note n="1" xml:id="d1331fn1">Not printed.</note> from the British and
                    French Embassies, <pb facs="1202" n="944" xml:id="pg_944"/> respectively, to the
                    effect that the necessary instructions have been issued to British and French
                    naval vessels not to prevent the passage to Europe, on the steamship <hi
                        rend="italic">Nieuw Amsterdam</hi>, of the Hamburg-American Line, sailing
                    from New York on October 5, 1915, of Dr. <persName corresp="#p_DCT1">Constantin
                        Theodor Dumba</persName>, it being understood that Doctor <persName
                        corresp="#p_DCT1">Dumba</persName> will abstain from any unneutral act
                    during the voyage.</p>
                <p>It will be observed that the British and French Governments have been informed
                    that Doctor <persName corresp="#p_DCT1">Dumba</persName> desires to be
                    accompanied by his valet, Roman Stevanow, an Austrian subject, who is declared
                    to be unfit for military service.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
